---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import DocsSidebar from "../../components/DocsSidebar.astro";
---
<Layout title="MCP server · flipagent docs">
	<div class="cmw cmw-bordered">
		<div class="docs-shell">
			<DocsSidebar />
			<article class="docs-content">
				<h1>MCP server</h1>
				<p class="lead">flipagent-mcp is a Model Context Protocol server that exposes the full reseller API as MCP tools. Works with any compatible AI client: Claude Desktop, Cursor, Cline, Zed, Windsurf.</p>

				<h2>Install</h2>
				<p>The MCP server is published on npm and runs through <code>npx</code>, so no global install is needed. The fastest path is the CLI:</p>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>{`npx -y flipagent-cli init --mcp`}</code></pre></div>
				<p>It auto-detects every supported client and writes the config in one go.</p>

				<h2>Claude Desktop (manual)</h2>
				<p>Edit <code>~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json</code>:</p>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>{`{
  "mcpServers": {
    "flipagent": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "flipagent-mcp"],
      "env": { "FLIPAGENT_API_KEY": "fa_free_xxx" }
    }
  }
}`}</code></pre></div>
				<p>Restart Claude. The tools below show up in any chat.</p>

				<h2>Cursor / Cline / Zed / Windsurf</h2>
				<p>Same JSON, different file:</p>
				<table class="api">
					<thead><tr><th>Client</th><th>Config file</th></tr></thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr><td>Cursor</td><td><code>.cursor/mcp.json</code> (in workspace)</td></tr>
						<tr><td>Cline</td><td><code>~/.cline/mcp.json</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td>Zed</td><td>Settings → MCP servers</td></tr>
						<tr><td>Windsurf</td><td>Settings → Cascade → MCP servers</td></tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>

				<h2>Tools exposed</h2>
				<table class="api">
					<thead><tr><th>Tool</th><th>Backed by</th></tr></thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Marketplace data</strong></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_search</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/items/search</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_item_detail</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/items/&#123;id&#125;</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_sold_search</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/items/search?status=sold</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_taxonomy_default_id</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/categories</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_taxonomy_suggest</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/categories/suggest</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_taxonomy_aspects</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/categories/&#123;id&#125;/aspects</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Decisions</strong></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>evaluate_listing</code></td><td><code>POST /v1/evaluate</code> &mdash; composite (search + LLM same-product filter + score)</td></tr>
						<tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Operations</strong></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ship_quote</code></td><td><code>POST /v1/ship/quote</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ship_providers</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/ship/providers</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Sell-side</strong> (eBay OAuth required via <code>/v1/connect/ebay</code>)</td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_connect_status</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/connect/ebay/status</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_create_inventory_item</code></td><td><code>PUT /v1/listings/&#123;sku&#125;</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_create_offer</code></td><td><code>POST /v1/listings</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_publish_offer</code></td><td><code>POST /v1/listings/&#123;sku&#125;/relist</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_list_orders</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/sales</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_mark_shipped</code></td><td><code>POST /v1/sales/&#123;id&#125;/ship</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_list_payouts</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/payouts</code></td></tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>

				<h2>Compose your own logic</h2>
				<p>Tools are typed and orthogonal. <code>evaluate_listing</code> is composite — server-side it fetches the item, searches sold + active, runs an LLM same-product filter, and scores in a single call. Agents can also chain low-level tools (<code>ebay_search</code> → <code>ebay_sold_search</code> → <code>evaluate_listing</code> → <code>ship_quote</code>) to assemble custom reselling workflows. See the <a href="/docs/api/">API reference</a> for request shapes.</p>
			</article>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>
